rganised with these cable management tips.Maker Stations=E2=80=A2Editorial =
Team [https://www.makerstations.io/r/61efab1b?m=3Df49fc9ba-e342-4196-a405-0=
1ce34035d78]

Do not ignore cable management. I believe spending some time in that area c=
an take anyone=E2=80=99s workspace to the next level.

Take inspiration from multiple workspaces, but make it your own.


What does your typical day look like?

A typical day for me starts at 6:30 am when I wake up to get ready for work=
=2E After having breakfast, I arrive at work by 8 am.

A typical workday finishes around 6 pm.

After work, I spend about an hour at the gym before getting home around 7:3=
0 pm or 8 pm.

Once I=E2=80=99m home, I have dinner and catch up on my socials.

Adam focused on three key elements in creating his workspace: ensuring a wa=
rm and calming atmosphere, a functional layout, and an aesthetically pleasi=
ng design

I=E2=80=99ll spend an hour or so writing down ideas for my next Instagram p=
ost or editing photos and videos.

My wife and I will also spend some time together, and I=E2=80=99m usually i=
n bed by 11 pm.

On my days off, I catch up on errands and housework and work on creating co=
ntent.

I aim to create enough content to last for a week in just one day.

Being far from a minimalist, Adam prefers a home filled with items he loves=
, creating a cosy and comfortable living (and working) space

When my wife also has the day off, we try to get away to rest, recharge and=
 spend time together.

When I have some free time, I like to do some gaming.

Most recently, I finished playing Hi-Fi Rush, a fantastic rhythm-based game=
 on the Xbox.


Your tips for working from home?

When creating content from home, I write down the ideas I want to photograp=
h and film that day.

Then, I work through my to-do list to create as much content as I can.

Throughout the day, I take breaks to watch a TV show or movie or listen to =
some music or a podcast.

How to Take Better Breaks When Working from HomeImprove your productivity a=
nd cut down on stress with these ideas for taking better breaks while WFH.M=
aker Stations=E2=80=A2Editorial Team [https://www.makerstations.io/r/e66084=
f2?m=3Df49fc9ba-e342-4196-a405-01ce34035d78]

On days when I feel particularly unmotivated or stressed, I make an effort =
to go outside and get some sun and fresh air for my mental health.

Remember to always leave time in your day to spend on yourself.

